On Windows ( or CMD), you can run everything as follows:
Download the data



python .\download_data.py
Verify the folder structure
Ensure you have:


.\data\IndianPines\
  ├── data.mat
  └── labels.mat
Install dependencies



python -m pip install torch torchvision scipy requests numpy
Train the model



python .\train.py `
  --data-path .\data\IndianPines `
  --spectral-dim 200 `
  --num-classes 16 `
  --epochs 100 `
  --batch-size 32 `
  --lr 1e-3 `
  --train-ratio 0.6 `
  --val-ratio 0.2 `
  --gpu 0 `
  --ckpt .\best.pth `
  --data data


(Use the backtick ` at line-ends in  to continue lines; in CMD you’d put it all on one line.)
(Optional) Run a standalone test



python .\test.py `
  --data-path .\data\IndianPines `
  --spectral-dim 200 `
  --num-classes 16 `
  --batch-size 32 `
  --gpu 0 `
  --ckpt .\best.pth`
  --data data


Inference on a single sample



python .\infer.py `
  --data-path .\data\IndianPines `
  --spectral-dim 200 `
  --num-classes 16 `
  --ckpt .\best.pth `
  --index 0 `
  --gpu 0 `
  --data data